            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "A faucet dripping 10 times per minute wastes 350+ gallons annually—increasing water bills by $7-$12 yearly and creating annoying background noise. Drips typically result from worn faucet cartridges (in modern faucets) or deteriorated washers and O-rings (in older compression faucets). In Tucson's hard water, mineral deposits accelerate cartridge wear—we see cartridges failing at 5-8 years versus the 10-15 year typical lifespan in soft water areas. Our repair approach: We identify whether your faucet uses replaceable cartridges or requires washer replacement, stock common cartridges on service vehicles enabling same-day repair, test thoroughly ensuring complete drip elimination, and inspect for secondary issues like corroded supply lines or failing shutoff valves that often accompany cartridge failure. Cartridge replacement costs $150-$300 parts and labor—dramatically less than the $600-$900 cost of unnecessary faucet replacement. Prevention tip: Annual [link:/services/plumbing-maintenance-tucson|plumbing maintenance] inspections catch early cartridge wear before drips develop, and using sink aerators reduces mineral buildup extending cartridge life in hard water areas."
